"warren baity" <warrenbaity(-at-)hotmail.com> wrote:
> this is just going to be a quick one cause its probably easy. how do you 
> adjust where your headlights are pointing? are there screws to adjust or 
> something like that?? thats it. thanks

You will have to remove the headlamp trim ring to
gain access to the headlamp aim adjustment bolts.
One bolt holds the trim ring in place.

http://lighting.mbz.org/tech/how_to/aim/

